# RC Glam Studio — Coding Standards

Frontend-only React marketing/portfolio site. All code lives in `app/`. **No backend, API, or database.**

Full reference: `.kiro/steering/coding-standards.md`

## Tech Stack

React 18 · TypeScript · Vite · MUI + Tailwind · Framer Motion · MagicUI · react-router-dom

## Architecture

```
app/src/
├── App.tsx              ← providers, theme, lazy-loaded routes
├── theme.ts             ← MUI light/dark theme
├── components/magicui/  ← animated UI primitives
├── features/[feature]/  ← components/, pages/
├── lib/utils.ts         ← cn() and pure utilities
└── shared/              ← components/, hooks/
```

- Features are self-contained; import across features only via `shared/` or barrel exports.
- New feature flow: components → page → lazy route in `App.tsx`.
- Static content stays within the feature folder.

## TypeScript

- Strict mode; never use `any`. Prefer `unknown` when truly unknown.
- Explicit return types on all functions.
- `interface` for objects, `type` for unions.
- `import type { Foo } from "./foo"` for type-only imports.
- Remove unused imports immediately.

## Naming

| Item | Convention | Example |
|------|------------|---------|
| Files | kebab-case | `hero-section.tsx` |
| Components | PascalCase | `HeroSection` |
| Hooks/functions | camelCase | `useColorMode` |
| Constants | SCREAMING_SNAKE | `MAX_GALLERY_ITEMS` |

## React & UI

- Functional components only; prop interfaces above the component.
- Extract hooks when a component exceeds ~50 lines.
- MUI for structural UI; Tailwind via `cn()`; MagicUI for animations.
- Use MUI theme tokens — never hardcode colors (`grey.50`, `#f8fafc`).
- CSS variables for custom UI: `var(--background)`, `var(--foreground)`, `var(--border)`.
- Dark mode: `.dark` on `<html>` via `ColorModeProvider`.
- Loading states, empty states, responsive layout (desktop-first).
- Forms: labels, validation, disabled submit states.

## File Annotations

Every file starts with:

```ts
/**
 * @file [filename] — [purpose]
 * @feature [name] | @shared
 * @dependencies [non-obvious imports]
 */
```

One-line JSDoc on exported functions/components. `// TODO(author): description` only.

## ESLint Patterns (when configured)

```tsx
// ❌ onClick={() => setOpen(true)}
// ✅ onClick={() => { setOpen(true); }}

// ❌ primaryTypographyProps={{ variant: "body2" }}
// ✅ slotProps={{ primary: { variant: "body2" } }}
```

## Commands

```bash
npm run dev      # http://localhost:5173
npm run build
npm run format
```

Run from repo root or `app/`.
